      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#platform-3">
        <div class="bento-num">03</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Visual businesses: Instagram</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For restaurants, salons, retail, fitness — where <span class="accent">what you offer looks as good as it sounds.</span></h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Reels get 2× the reach of static photos. Location tags and local hashtags drive area-based discovery. The right platform if your product photographs well.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full breakdown <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PLATFORM SELECTION GUIDE -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How to choose</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Pick platforms by <span class="accent">business type, not follower count.</span></h2>
      <p>A plumber doesn't need TikTok. A bakery doesn't need LinkedIn. The best platform is the one where your specific customers search for businesses like yours. Here's the decision framework we use across 70+ industries.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">3-step selection framework</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Three questions. Two platforms.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Answer these in order. Start with GBP. Add one more based on your type.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>B2B or B2C?</h4>
              <p>B2B → GBP + LinkedIn. B2C → GBP + one more based on steps 2 and 3.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Is your product or service visual?</h4>
              <p>Yes (food, retail, fitness, beauty) → Instagram or TikTok. No (plumbing, accounting, legal) → Facebook or Nextdoor.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>What age is your target customer?</h4>
              <p>Under 35 → Instagram + TikTok. 35–55 → Facebook + Instagram. Over 55 → Facebook + Nextdoor.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">By business type</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Platform picks for 10 local business types.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Based on testing across 70+ industries.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">🍕</span><div><h4>Restaurant/Cafe</h4><p>GBP · Instagram · TikTok optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">🔧</span><div><h4>Plumber/Electrician/HVAC</h4><p>GBP · Facebook · Nextdoor optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✂️</span><div><h4>Salon/Barbershop</h4><p>GBP · Instagram · TikTok optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">🦷</span><div><h4>Dentist/Doctor</h4><p>GBP · Facebook · Instagram optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">⚖️</span><div><h4>Law Firm</h4><p>GBP · Facebook · LinkedIn optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">🏡</span><div><h4>Real Estate Agent</h4><p>GBP · Instagram · Nextdoor optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">🛍️</span><div><h4>Retail Store</h4><p>GBP · Instagram · TikTok optional</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">💪</span><div><h4>Gym/Fitness Studio</h4><p>GBP · Instagram · Facebook optional</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">46<span class="accent">%</span></div><div class="stat-label">Google searches have local intent</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">4<span class="accent">×</span></div><div class="stat-label">More website visits from optimized GBP</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">2.8<span class="accent">×</span></div><div class="stat-label">More Map Pack appearances with regular GBP posts</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">3.7<span class="accent">%</span></div><div class="stat-label">TikTok engagement rate — highest of any platform</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PLATFORM BREAKDOWNS -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Platform breakdowns</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">6 platforms ranked by <span class="accent">local business ROI.</span></h2>
      <p>Each platform: who it's for, how much time it takes, ROI data, and honest limitations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="platform-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · HIGHEST ROI · FREE</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Google Business Profile — best platform for every local business</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">1–2 hours per week. Appears directly in Google search results and Maps.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">GBP isn't a social media platform in the traditional sense — but it's the highest-ROI local marketing channel that exists. 46% of Google searches have local intent. Optimized profiles appear 80% more often in search results. Profiles with regular updates appear 2.8× more frequently in the top 3 Map results. And it's free. The problem: most businesses set it up once and never post to it again. That's leaving a massive visibility gap open for competitors who do.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Appears directly in Google search results at the moment of intent</h4>
              <p>No other platform puts you in front of customers at the exact moment they're searching "HVAC repair near me" or "best dentist [city]."</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Optimized profiles generate 4× more website visits, 12% more calls</h4>
              <p>The ROI data is unusually clear for this platform. Posts, photos, and reviews compound.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Reviews, posts, photos, Q&amp;A — all indexed by Google</h4>
              <p>Every piece of content on your GBP is searchable and contributes to Map Pack ranking.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest limitation: requires consistent updates to work</h4>
              <p>A GBP profile with no posts in 90 days signals to Google that the business isn't active. Consistency is the whole game — and where most businesses fail.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Automate your GBP — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="platform-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · HIGH ROI · FREE (ORGANIC)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Facebook — essential for service businesses and demographics 35+</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">2–3 hours per week. 3.07 billion monthly active users. Best for Events, Groups, and local recommendations.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Facebook's organic reach has declined — only 2–5% of your followers see each post. But the platform still delivers real results for local service businesses because of Groups, Events, and Reviews. A recommendation from a local Facebook Group carries enormous weight. The Events feature drives foot traffic for classes, specials, and open houses. And 70% of Facebook users visit local business pages weekly. For businesses targeting customers 35 and up, it's still the dominant social platform.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Community Group recommendations carry real weight</h4><p>A recommendation in a neighborhood Group reaches a hyper-targeted, trusting audience.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Events feature drives foot traffic better than any other platform</h4><p>Classes, sales, open hours, and local events convert better on Facebook than Instagram.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>70% of Facebook users visit local business pages weekly</h4><p>Your page is a destination. Keep it active and it converts.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest limitation: declining organic reach</h4><p>2–5% reach per post means most followers don't see what you publish. You're creating for a small fraction of your audience without paid amplification.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="platform-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · HIGH ROI (VISUAL) · FREE (ORGANIC)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Instagram — best for visual businesses and discovery</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">3–4 hours per week. Reels get 2× reach of static photos. Essential for food, fitness, beauty, and retail.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Instagram is a discovery engine for visual businesses. Reels reach non-followers through the algorithm. Location tags and local hashtags connect content to area-based searches. User-generated content — customers tagging your restaurant or salon — builds social proof without any extra effort on your part. If your product photographs well, Instagram is where new customers find you. If it doesn't, the time investment is hard to justify versus other platforms.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Reels algorithm surfaces content to non-followers — strongest organic reach</h4><p>A single Reel can reach 10× your follower count if it connects with the algorithm.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Location tags and local hashtags drive area-based discovery</h4><p>Customers searching for "[service] in [city]" find Instagram content as part of that search.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>User-generated content builds trust without extra effort</h4><p>Every customer photo tag is free marketing with built-in social proof.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest limitation: 3–4 hours per week if you're posting consistently</h4><p>High-quality visual content takes time to produce. theStacc automates Instagram posting at $49/month if the time cost is the blocker.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="platform-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · MEDIUM-HIGH ROI · FREE (ORGANIC)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">TikTok — best for restaurants, retail, and personality-driven brands</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">2–3 hours per week. Highest engagement rate (2–3.7%). Restaurant adoption doubled 2023–2024.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">TikTok has the highest engagement rate of any major platform. A single video from a zero-follower account can reach 50,000–500,000 people. 88% of small businesses report TikTok promotions led to higher sales. Restaurant adoption doubled from 26% to 48% between 2023 and 2024. But it doesn't work for every business type — it rewards personality, entertainment, and raw video over polished production. A law firm on TikTok is usually a mistake. A barbershop or food truck is often a hit.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Algorithm reaches non-followers — a new account can go viral</h4><p>No follower base required. The algorithm rewards content quality, not account age.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Highest engagement rate of any major platform (2–3.7%)</h4><p>More real interactions per view than Instagram, Facebook, or LinkedIn.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>88% of small businesses report TikTok promotions drove higher sales</h4><p>The conversion from TikTok to in-store or online purchase is real and measurable.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest limitation: not for every business type</h4><p>Contractors, accountants, and law firms rarely see ROI here. And you need 3+ videos per week for the algorithm to surface your content consistently.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="platform-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · MEDIUM ROI · FREE (ORGANIC)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Nextdoor — best for home services and contractors</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">1 hour per week. 78 million US weekly active users. 79% of users influenced by neighbor recommendations.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Nextdoor is the hyper-local platform. It connects verified neighbors within specific geographic areas. 75% of its users are homeowners — which is exactly the audience for landscapers, plumbers, roofers, and house cleaners. A recommendation from a verified neighbor in your service area carries more weight than any ad you could run. The platform is small compared to Facebook, but the targeting precision is unmatched for home service businesses.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Hyper-local targeting — only reaches verified neighbors in your service area</h4><p>No wasted impressions on people outside your market. Every person who sees you could be a customer.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>79% of users influenced by neighbor recommendations</h4><p>Nextdoor recommendations convert like referrals, not ads.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>75% of users are homeowners — perfect for home service businesses</h4><p>The audience demographics align precisely with landscaping, HVAC, plumbing, and cleaning.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest limitation: limited reach for non-home-service businesses</h4><p>Restaurants, retail, and B2B businesses see lower ROI here. The platform is built for home-services-adjacent use cases.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="platform-6" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#6 · MEDIUM ROI (B2B ONLY) · FREE (ORGANIC)</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">LinkedIn — best for B2B services and professional practices</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">1–2 hours per week. 1 billion members. Effective for law firms, accountants, and business services.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">LinkedIn is the B2B platform. If your customers are business owners, corporate decision-makers, or professionals — lawyers, accountants, consultants, business coaches — LinkedIn reaches them more precisely than any other social platform. Targeting by job title, industry, and company size is available even organically. Long-form thought leadership content performs well. For consumer-facing local businesses like restaurants or salons, it's the wrong platform entirely.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
